		             "description": "<div style=\"text-align: center;\">\n\t<a href=\"http://www.engadget.com/2011/10/11/apple-releases-itunes-10-5-with-itunes-in-the-cloud/\"><img src=\"images/feedimages/apple-itunes-10-5-1318354039.jpg\" style=\"border-width: 0px; border-style: solid; margin: 4px;\" /><\/a><\/div>\n<div>\n\tAs far as iTunes updates go this is a pretty big one -- version 10.5 brings with it what Apple's calling <a href=\"http://www.engadget.com/tag/itunesinthecloud\">iTunes in the Cloud<\/a>, which allows for automatic downloads of purchases to your Mac or Windows computers and all of your iOS devices, as well as the ability to download previous purchases on said devices as many times as you want. It's not exactly a traditional cloud-based service, but you do always have access to all of your purchased media, regardless of the device (so long as it runs some form of iTunes). As expected, it also finally adds WiFi syncing for your iOS devices, although you'll still have to wait a bit longer for the <a href=\"http://www.engadget.com/tag/itunesmatch\">iTunes Match<\/a> service -- it's slated to roll out closer to the <a href=\"http://www.engadget.com/2011/10/04/itunes-match-hits-us-end-of-october-for-24-99/\">end of the month<\/a>. As usual, you can look for it in Apple's Software Update, or you can hit the link below to download it directly.<\/div><p style=\"padding:5px;background:#ddd;border:1px solid #ccc;clear:both;\"><a href=\"http://www.engadget.com/2011/10/11/apple-releases-itunes-10-5-with-itunes-in-the-cloud/\">Apple releases iTunes 10.5 with iTunes in the Cloud<\/a> originally appeared on <a href=\"http://www.engadget.com\">Engadget<\/a> on Tue, 11 Oct 2011 13:12:00 EDT.  Please see our <a href=\"http://www.weblogsinc.com/feed-terms/\">terms for use of feeds<\/a>.<\/p><h6 style=\"clear: both; padding: 8px 0 0 0; height: 2px; font-size: 1px; border: 0; margin: 0; padding: 0;\"><\/h6><a href=\"http://www.engadget.com/2011/10/11/apple-releases-itunes-10-5-with-itunes-in-the-cloud/\" rel=\"bookmark\" title=\"Permanent link to this entry\">Permalink<\/a>   |  <img class=\"img_label\" src=\"images/post_label_source.gif\" alt=\"source\"/><span class=\"caption\"><a href=\"http://www.apple.com/itunes/\">Apple<\/a><!--//--><\/span>  | <a href=\"http://www.engadget.com/forward/20078957/\" title=\"Send this entry to a friend via email\">Email this<\/a> | <a href=\"http://www.engadget.com/2011/10/11/apple-releases-itunes-10-5-with-itunes-in-the-cloud/#comments\" title=\"View reader comments on this entry\">Comments<\/a>",
